# jsdoc/require-param-name

<div class="rule-meta">
</div>

### What it does

Requires that all `@param` tags have names.

### Why is this bad?

The name of a param should be documented.

### Example

```javascript
// Passing
/** @param {SomeType} foo */
function quux(foo) {}

// Failing
/** @param {SomeType} */
function quux(foo) {}
```
